-- Bentley’s Brown Discusses New Book ‘Life After Law’ (Audio)
-- B y
-- 2013-09-19T21:33:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-19/bentley-s-brown-discusses-new-book-life-after-law-audio-.html
 Liz Brown, assistant professor of
business law at  Bentley University , discusses her new book, 
"Life after Law: Finding Work You Love with the J.D. You Have." 
 Brown, a former partner at an international law firm, talks 
with Bloomberg's Kathleen Hays and Vonnie Quinn on Bloomberg 
Radio's "The Hays Advantage." Bentley University is a strategic 
partner of Bloomberg Radio.  (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 16:12
 